8 UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 7.2. (a) For an eligible child to qualify for a
9 prekindergarten voucher under this chapter, the eligible child must
10 reside with a parent or guardian who is:
11 (1) working or attending a job training or an educational program;
12 or
13 (2) actively seeking employment, subject to the approval by
14 the United States Department of Health and Human Services
15 as provided in 45 CFR 98.21.
16 (b) For a limited eligibility child to qualify for a prekindergarten
17 voucher under this chapter, the limited eligibility child must reside with
18 a parent or guardian who:
19 (1) is working or attending a job training or an educational
20 program; or
21 or
22 (2) receives Social Security Disability Insurance, Supplemental
23 Security Income benefits, or disability benefits from the United
24 States Department of Veterans Affairs; or
25 (3) is actively seeking employment, subject to the approval by
26 the United States Department of Health and Human Services
27 as provided in 45 CFR 98.21.
28 (c) Before the office may provide a prekindergarten voucher to an
29 eligible child, a limited eligibility child, or a child of a child care
30 employee under this chapter, the office shall require that a parent or
31 guardian of the child agree to the following:
32 (1) The child will attend the prekindergarten program of an
33 eligible provider selected by the parent or guardian for the full
34 duration of the prekindergarten program year.
35 (2) The parent or guardian will not transfer to another
36 prekindergarten program during the prekindergarten program
37 year.
38 (3) The child will attend the prekindergarten program at least
39 eighty-five percent (85%) of the days that the prekindergarten
40 program is provided.
41 (4) The parent or guardian will allow the child to participate in an
42 external evaluation conducted by researchers, including the
